messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /users/signup

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

Per-method acceptability (based on the code, not on framework defaults or runtime behavior):
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In index.js the user routes are mounted with app.use('/users', userRoutes). That makes the router paths prefixed with /users.
- In routes/userRoutes.js the signup route is defined as router.post('/signup', signup). Combining the prefix yields /users/signup.
- The code only registers a POST handler for '/signup'. No handlers for GET, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE (or a router.all) are present in the provided files, so only POST is considered acceptable per the instruction to base decisions strictly on the code.
